520
00:27:57.046 --> 00:27:58.736
You've become a man since.

521
00:27:59.667 --> 00:28:02.115
- This ranch has been good to me.
- Mm.

522
00:28:03.425 --> 00:28:04.805
You've been good to it.

523
00:28:08.667 --> 00:28:10.667
I knew you had fight.

524
00:28:11.563 --> 00:28:13.322
Knew you'd always have my back.

525
00:28:13.425 --> 00:28:15.529
Always.

526
00:28:18.081 --> 00:28:20.529
I know we ain't blood. but...

527
00:28:20.632 --> 00:28:22.563
I'd like to think
we're brothers.

528
00:28:22.667 --> 00:28:25.184
You're the one I should've had.

529
00:28:25.253 --> 00:28:27.253
♪ dramatic music ♪

530
00:28:27.356 --> 00:28:28.529
That means the world to me.

531
00:28:28.598 --> 00:28:31.081
It means nobody understands

532
00:28:31.218 --> 00:28:34.598
what we done
to protect this ranch.

533
00:28:34.701 --> 00:28:36.184
No one will.

534
00:28:37.081 --> 00:28:41.425
And no one knows what we'd do
to hold on to it.

535
00:28:42.563 --> 00:28:44.287
Anything.

536
00:28:44.425 --> 00:28:46.460
Everything.

537
00:28:52.081 --> 00:28:53.632
This is your home.

538
00:28:55.874 --> 00:28:57.184
Your family.

539
00:29:00.736 --> 00:29:02.460
It's the only one I got.

540
00:29:06.977 --> 00:29:10.460
We ain't gonna let nobody take
what's rightfully ours.

541
00:29:14.977 --> 00:29:17.184
♪ tense music ♪

542
00:29:31.563 --> 00:29:33.770
♪

543
00:29:44.460 --> 00:29:46.632
♪

544
00:29:55.287 --> 00:29:57.218
[exhales sharply]

545
00:30:05.770 --> 00:30:07.391
[Chet]
Hey. motherfucker!

546
00:30:07.460 --> 00:30:08.701
Yeah.

547
00:30:08.805 --> 00:30:10.977
I got your attention now. huh?

548
00:30:11.115 --> 00:30:13.081
Don't do anything
you might regret.

549
00:30:13.150 --> 00:30:16.598
No matter how dirty. how shitty.

550
00:30:16.701 --> 00:30:19.494
I did everything
you and Ms. Beulah asked.

551
00:30:19.598 --> 00:30:21.805
I risked my goddamn life.
I thought of y'all as family.

552
00:30:21.908 --> 00:30:24.529
We are.
We're-we're family. Chet.

553
00:30:24.632 --> 00:30:27.081
Choice. coming from the bastard.

554
00:30:28.081 --> 00:30:29.322
Put the gun down.

555
00:30:29.425 --> 00:30:31.081
We-we can figure this out.

556
00:30:31.184 --> 00:30:32.425
All right? Let's talk.

557
00:30:32.494 --> 00:30:34.632
All you do is talk. Joaquin.

558
00:30:34.736 --> 00:30:36.287
Talk in fucking circles.

559
00:30:36.356 --> 00:30:39.460
and backstab
and cheat and fucking steal.

560
00:30:40.287 --> 00:30:44.598
You said there are only
two ways to leave this ranch.

561
00:30:44.701 --> 00:30:45.805
Two choices.

562
00:30:45.908 --> 00:30:46.632
[gunshot]

563
00:30:46.908 --> 00:30:48.598
♪

564
00:30:48.701 --> 00:30:50.287
[Joaquin]
Oh. fuck me!

565
00:30:51.494 --> 00:30:53.632
You shot me. You son of a bitch.

566
00:30:53.701 --> 00:30:55.425
Wait. wait. wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait. wait!

567
00:30:55.529 --> 00:30:57.391
- You two-faced piece of shit.
- [gunshot]

568
00:30:57.460 --> 00:30:59.012
[exclaims]

569
00:30:59.115 --> 00:31:01.150
[panting. groaning]

570
00:31:01.253 --> 00:31:02.839
Fuck.

571
00:31:04.391 --> 00:31:06.494
<i>Gracias. Miguel.</i>

572
00:31:06.563 --> 00:31:09.253
[Joaquin groaning]

573
00:31:11.253 --> 00:31:12.943
[vehicle approaching]

574
00:31:15.598 --> 00:31:17.356
<i>Más problemas. jefe.</i>

575
00:31:25.874 --> 00:31:28.218
[groaning. panting]

576
00:31:29.701 --> 00:31:30.943
[softly] Whoa. whoa.

577
00:31:31.046 --> 00:31:33.839
[grunting]

578
00:31:34.874 --> 00:31:37.563
[wincing]

579
00:31:40.839 --> 00:31:42.081
Chet.

580
00:31:42.184 --> 00:31:44.218
He didn't take
his firing so well.

581
00:31:45.391 --> 00:31:47.253
You want to get that hand fixed?

582
00:31:48.770 --> 00:31:49.943
I can't go to a hospital.

583
00:31:50.046 --> 00:31:51.805
I ain't taking you
to the hospital.

584
00:31:51.908 --> 00:31:53.322
Go on and get in.

585
00:32:11.460 --> 00:32:14.425
[grunting]

586
00:32:26.494 --> 00:32:28.736
[Beulah laughs]

587
00:32:28.839 --> 00:32:30.598
Watching you in that meeting.

588
00:32:30.701 --> 00:32:33.770
it was like looking
in the mirror 20 years ago.

589
00:32:33.839 --> 00:32:37.322
You are a warrior
and a wildflower. Beth.

590
00:32:37.460 --> 00:32:40.598
You are the one
who charmed him. Beulah.

591
00:32:43.081 --> 00:32:44.943
[sighs] Getting older.
it just makes you

592
00:32:45.012 --> 00:32:47.150
ache for parts of yourself
that you didn't realize

593
00:32:47.287 --> 00:32:50.322
you were losing.
Crave what used to be.

594
00:32:52.253 --> 00:32:54.943
I held on too tight
for too long.

595
00:32:55.839 --> 00:32:57.425
Don't worry. The 10-Petal

596
00:32:57.494 --> 00:32:59.460
is not going anywhere.
I promise.

597
00:32:59.563 --> 00:33:03.287
My daddy died
to save that ranch.

598
00:33:03.356 --> 00:33:05.598
He asked me to do the same.

599
00:33:06.529 --> 00:33:08.563
A tale as old as time. isn't it?

600
00:33:10.529 --> 00:33:13.839
It's hard to watch
a man love dirt more than blood.

601
00:33:16.356 --> 00:33:19.218
I am gonna go to the ladies'.

602
00:33:22.081 --> 00:33:24.391
Another round. please.

603
00:33:26.150 --> 00:33:28.322
♪ tense music ♪

604
00:33:30.253 --> 00:33:32.425
[Joaquin groaning softly]

605
00:33:39.012 --> 00:33:40.150
[grunts]

606
00:33:52.460 --> 00:33:54.012
[engine turns off]

607
00:33:54.287 --> 00:33:57.012
♪

608
00:33:57.115 --> 00:34:01.805
I want to know who put the body
on my property.

609
00:34:07.667 --> 00:34:09.184
[sighs]

610
00:34:11.874 --> 00:34:13.460
My brother is a fool.

611
00:34:13.563 --> 00:34:16.391
Joaquin. I know a lot of fools.

612
00:34:16.460 --> 00:34:18.287
and they ain't killers.

613
00:34:19.736 --> 00:34:21.736
You know a lot of killers?

614
00:34:23.529 --> 00:34:25.253
Enough.

615
00:34:29.839 --> 00:34:32.598
Wes Ayers was one of our hands.

616
00:34:33.598 --> 00:34:36.494
He was also Rob-Will
and Chet's dealer.

617
00:34:36.598 --> 00:34:38.218
- Mm-hmm.
- I don't know how long ago

618
00:34:38.322 --> 00:34:40.322
it started.
but it spun out of control.

619
00:34:41.425 --> 00:34:44.770
Wes paid the ultimate price.

620
00:34:44.874 --> 00:34:47.150
Chet. too. I guess.

621
00:34:48.632 --> 00:34:52.287
I don't know why
Rob-Will chose your land.

622
00:34:52.425 --> 00:34:54.115
If you ask him.

623
00:34:54.253 --> 00:34:56.494
he probably wouldn't either.

624
00:34:58.322 --> 00:35:00.150
He's always
seen himself like a prince

625
00:35:00.253 --> 00:35:03.874
who never became king.
so the kingdom be damned.

626
00:35:03.977 --> 00:35:06.701
I want to know exactly
where your brother is.

627
00:35:06.839 --> 00:35:08.322
Sacred Mesa.

628
00:35:08.391 --> 00:35:10.391
rehab facility in Sedona.

629
00:35:11.563 --> 00:35:15.218
After that.
I've lined up a job in Botswana.

630
00:35:16.253 --> 00:35:18.943
He'll take
disgruntled princes like himself

631
00:35:19.046 --> 00:35:21.184
to slaughter elephants

632
00:35:21.322 --> 00:35:24.598
so they can pretend
to be heroic knights.

633
00:35:27.150 --> 00:35:29.322
He's never coming back. Rip.

634
00:35:31.563 --> 00:35:33.184
And if he does.
I'll fucking kill him.

635
00:35:33.460 --> 00:35:35.563
♪

636
00:35:40.046 --> 00:35:42.287
[engine starts]

637
00:36:02.356 --> 00:36:04.908
♪

638
00:36:18.908 --> 00:36:21.253
You gonna tell me what happened?

639
00:36:21.356 --> 00:36:22.356
Shit. you got to ask him.

640
00:36:22.460 --> 00:36:23.770
A disgruntled cowboy.

641
00:36:23.908 --> 00:36:25.494
[Rip]
He'll be all right. Everett?

642
00:36:25.598 --> 00:36:26.805
[Everett]
Yeah. I got him.

643
00:36:26.943 --> 00:36:28.012
He's not the first man
I've stitched up.

644
00:36:28.081 --> 00:36:29.563
Let's go.

645
00:36:30.391 --> 00:36:32.253
Come on. get inside here.

646
00:36:34.287 --> 00:36:36.184
Let's take a look at that.

647
00:36:36.287 --> 00:36:38.701
[engine starts]

648
00:36:42.115 --> 00:36:44.322
[machine whirs. beeps]

649
00:36:49.908 --> 00:36:52.322
[Everett]
Yeah. take it easy.

650
00:36:53.736 --> 00:36:55.736
[Joaquin sighs]

651
00:36:55.874 --> 00:36:57.322
[exhales sharply]

652
00:36:58.081 --> 00:36:59.943
I'll set the bones.
but you're gonna

653
00:37:00.081 --> 00:37:02.287
need a surgeon
to make it look pretty.

654
00:37:04.667 --> 00:37:06.598
I don't want the whole county
asking questions.

655
00:37:06.667 --> 00:37:09.701
That means you don't
want me asking questions?

656
00:37:11.460 --> 00:37:12.667
It's complicated. Everett.

657
00:37:12.770 --> 00:37:14.322
Yeah. always is
with your family.

658
00:37:14.425 --> 00:37:15.805
This'll sting.

659
00:37:15.943 --> 00:37:17.563
[groans]

660
00:37:20.770 --> 00:37:22.253
You're good at this.

661
00:37:22.356 --> 00:37:24.150
Yeah. well. animals are easier.

662
00:37:26.563 --> 00:37:29.460
Take it easy now. There you go.

663
00:37:30.805 --> 00:37:31.770
Okay.

664
00:37:31.874 --> 00:37:34.218
I see why she likes you.

665
00:37:34.322 --> 00:37:36.563
Your mother likes everyone.

666
00:37:36.667 --> 00:37:38.977
as long as
they don't get in her way.

667
00:37:42.253 --> 00:37:43.563
Yeah.

668
00:37:44.805 --> 00:37:47.322
She's happiest
when you're around.

669
00:37:55.977 --> 00:37:58.563
I might have been wrong
about Oreana and Carter.

670
00:37:58.667 --> 00:37:59.943
- Thank you.
- [bartender] Of course.

671
00:38:00.012 --> 00:38:02.736
She certainly has
taken a liking to him.

672
00:38:02.839 --> 00:38:04.977
I told her.

673
00:38:05.081 --> 00:38:07.701
that kid. he has a...

674
00:38:07.805 --> 00:38:09.356
he has a really pure heart.

675
00:38:09.460 --> 00:38:11.322
Mm.

676
00:38:11.391 --> 00:38:13.736
Well. it must've been
an easy pregnancy. then.

677
00:38:16.736 --> 00:38:18.908
He wasn't a pregnancy.

678
00:38:19.012 --> 00:38:21.046
Mm-hmm.

679
00:38:21.839 --> 00:38:23.494
I have a theory.

680
00:38:23.563 --> 00:38:26.598
The harder the pregnancy.
the harder the heart.

681
00:38:26.736 --> 00:38:28.839
I struggled to carry Rob-Will.

682
00:38:28.908 --> 00:38:32.356
[groans]
Then I labored for 48 hours

683
00:38:32.460 --> 00:38:35.391
before he came out
kicking and screaming.

684
00:38:35.529 --> 00:38:36.908
I was young.

685
00:38:37.046 --> 00:38:39.253
I wasn't ready. I felt so alone.

686
00:38:39.391 --> 00:38:43.356
His daddy died in an awful flood
before he was born.

687
00:38:46.391 --> 00:38:48.046
[sighs]

688
00:38:48.184 --> 00:38:51.253
Then. little baby Joaquin

689
00:38:51.391 --> 00:38:53.150
was dropped in my lap.

690
00:38:53.874 --> 00:38:57.391
Yeah. by a ranch hand who. uh...

691
00:38:57.494 --> 00:38:59.563
he got on the wrong side
of the law.

692
00:38:59.667 --> 00:39:01.494
[exclaims] I was scared

693
00:39:01.632 --> 00:39:04.115
till that survival instinct
kicked in.

694
00:39:04.943 --> 00:39:08.391
After that. I had no problem

695
00:39:08.460 --> 00:39:10.736
putting a bullet in the skull

696
00:39:10.805 --> 00:39:14.322
of anything
that threatened my boys.

697
00:39:15.218 --> 00:39:16.632
I understand that.

698
00:39:16.736 --> 00:39:18.770
Well. problem is.
you can't shoot addiction.

699
00:39:18.874 --> 00:39:22.425
You just pray the experts know
what the hell they're doing.

700
00:39:24.322 --> 00:39:25.322
Well. that must be hard.

701
00:39:25.460 --> 00:39:27.839
Eh. it's a storm I'll weather.

702
00:39:27.977 --> 00:39:31.632
But that's another
similarity in our families.

703
00:39:31.770 --> 00:39:32.770
What's that?

704
00:39:32.874 --> 00:39:38.046
Taking in wayward sons.
Joaquin.

705
00:39:38.115 --> 00:39:39.494
Carter.

706
00:39:39.632 --> 00:39:42.115
Montana's former
Attorney General. Jamie.

707
00:39:42.253 --> 00:39:44.943
♪ quiet. dramatic music ♪

708
00:39:50.322 --> 00:39:52.977
Yeah. I don't think
about him anymore.

709
00:39:53.081 --> 00:39:55.081
Yeah. well. I don't blame you.

710
00:39:55.150 --> 00:39:56.563
[scoffs]

711
00:39:56.632 --> 00:39:58.874
I mean. but one has to wonder
what really happened.

712
00:39:58.977 --> 00:40:01.322
Him gone missing

713
00:40:01.460 --> 00:40:03.770
after what happened
to your father?

714
00:40:07.391 --> 00:40:10.012
I don't think
about that. either.

715
00:40:13.253 --> 00:40:14.494
Hmm.

716
00:40:16.632 --> 00:40:18.805
♪
